{
  "texts": [
    "In our clinical infrastructure, which contains a maximum of two NVIDIA RTX6000 GPUs, we were able to perform all further-pretraining experiments within a reasonable timeframe (cf.",
    "Section S3).",
    "Compared to current foundation models with billions of parameters, we consider these models as lightweight.",
    "For both gbert and medbertde, we create medical-adapted variants by further-pretraining, as proposed by Gururangan et al. (2020) to assess the impact of different pretraining datasets on section classification results (Fig. 3).",
    "We defined datasets for three different pretraining approaches: 1. task-adaptation."
